## <a id="change-pod-ips"></a> Update the Network Profile on an Existing Cluster

To update the network profile on an existing cluster:

* [Confirm the Network Profile Property Supports Updates](#supports-updates) 
* [Update a Network Profile Property](#update-supported-params)  

### <a id="supports-updates"></a> Confirm the Network Profile Property Supports Updates

If a cluster has network profile assigned, you can update the following parameters on the network profile:  

* `pod_ip_block_ids`:  
<br>
    The primary [network profile use case](./network-profiles-define.html#use-cases) for updating the `pod_ip_block_ids` field 
    is to add additional IP addresses for pods when a cluster is at or near the point exhausting all available public IP addresses 
    for pods.  
<br>
    You can change the `pod_ip_block_ids`  array parameter as follows:

    - Add more IP Block IDs in the array
    - Reorder the IP Block IDs in the array

    You cannot remove a cluster's pod IP block IDs by creating and assigning a new network profile with `pod_ip_block_ids` 
    array values removed.  
<br> 
    For more information on the `pod_ip_block_ids` field, see [Network Profile Parameters](./network-profiles-define.html#params). 
    For an example, see [Adding Pods IPs](./network-profiles-pods.html#pods-ips-add).   

<br>
Any other change will fail [strict validation rules](network-profiles.html#update-profile) and not be applied. 


### <a id="update-supported-params"></a> Update a Network Profile Property

To update a supported network profile field for a cluster, do the following:

1. Define a new network profile JSON file with the exact contents of the original network profile.  
<br>
   If it is not possible to obtain the original network profile, create a new network profile with a unique <code>name</code> and the original values in all of the fields.  
1. Modify the network profile property that supports updating:  
    * If updating the `pod_ip_block_ids` field, reorder the IP Block IDs or add additional IP Block IDs.  

    <p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> Update only network profile properties that support being updated.</p>

    For more information on configuring a network profile, see [Network Profile Parameters](#params) above.   

1. Review and save the network profile configuration file.  

1. Apply the network profile:  

    ```
    tkgi update-cluster CLUSTER-NAME --network-profile
    ```
    Where `CLUSTER-NAME` is the unique name of your cluster.

### <a id="delete"></a> Delete a Network Profile

<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> administrators can delete a network profile that is not in use.

To delete a network profile:  

1. Run the following <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> CLI command:

    ```
    tkgi delete-network-profile NETWORK-PROFILE-NAME
    ```

    Where `NETWORK-PROFILE-NAME` is the name of the network profile you want to delete.

<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> You cannot delete a network profile that is in use.</p>



